narrative_preview:
I am filing a complaint against Bank of America XXXX BofA ) regarding an unresolved fraud charge on my credit card. 

On XX/XX/XXXX, a fraudulent transaction of {$68.00} occurred at XXXX XXXX, which I reported within five minutes. I disabled my card immediately. The store employee confirmed the transaction was made using the tap-to-pay feature, which I was told is immune to fraud. My card was never lost, stolen, or given to anyone else. I suspect BofA activated an additional card with the same number as the card I had when I activated my own. Regardless, I can not be held liable for a transaction I did not authorize.

However, my credit card statement shows three entries related to this incident : - XX/XX/XXXX : Fraudulent transaction : + {$68.00} ( posted on XX/XX/XXXX ) - XX/XX/XXXX : " FRAUD DISPUTE '' : + {$68.00} ( posted on XX/XX/XXXX ) - XX/XX/XXXX : " FRAUD DISPUTE '' : {$68.00}
